You only need to know the constructors to use the Scanner class.  But if you are curious to know why the Scanner can take a file even though it&#39;s not a Readable object, you will have to look into the code of the SCanner class.  

For example, the Scanner class has a constructor that takes a File object.  A File object is not a real file, just wrapper of a String of the path to the a file.  The scanner uses the File object to create an input stream and get a ReadableByteChannel.  The ReadableByeChannel will get passed to another constructor which call makeReadable.  See the code below.

In summary, the Scanner will create a Readable object from File, Path, and InputStreams, String and so on.  


```
    public Scanner(File source) throws FileNotFoundException {
        this((ReadableByteChannel)(new FileInputStream(source).getChannel()));
    }

    private static Readable makeReadable(ReadableByteChannel source,
                                         CharsetDecoder dec) {
        return Channels.newReader(source, dec, -1);
    }


